content:
Limits and Considerations for Decision Optimization (Beta)

Keep these limits and considerations in mind when using Decision Optimization.

Records to be optimized	100,000
Values among actionable variables	20
Filters	5

Prediction Definition and Model Requirements
Model must be created with Einstein Discovery. Can’t use uploaded models.
Model must be a binary classification or regression prediction model. Multiclass classification models aren’t supported.
The model can’t contain any transformations, such as fuzzy matching, sentiment detection, text clustering, projected predictions, or missing value imputation.
The model must be deployed to a Salesforce object, with model variables mapped to fields.
Model variables must be mapped. Can map to Salesforce fields or to a supplemental dataset.
Fields must be available on the Salesforce object that the model is deployed to.
For date fields, use absolute date values. Relative dates aren’t supported.

Actionable Variable
Variables marked as actionable during model deployment. Must be mapped to fields directly on the Salesforce object. Actionable variables mapped to fields on related objects aren’t supported.

Fields
Must be available on the object the model is deployed to. Can be a custom or standard Salesforce object. For date fields, use absolute date values. Relative dates aren’t supported.

Objective
Must include the outcome variable from the model’s goal. The outcome variable can’t be edited.

Filters
If more than one condition exists, it’s applied using AND logic. Additional filter logic such as OR and NOT isn’t supported.
title: Salesforce Decision Optimization Limits and Considerations
